\section{Inline music (single staff, paragraph-sized)}

Inline excerpts use a tighter staff size so a short gesture can sit beside text without dominating the page. The sample cell on this page is pulled in from its own fragment so a copy editor and an engraver can work in parallel. This example uses vertical centering so the cell sits naturally within running prose instead of looking perched on the baseline.\input{./chapters/introduction/inline/d-cell.lytex}
